---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import FactsPanel from "../components/FactsPanel.astro";
import GlassPanel from "../components/GlassPanel.astro";
import GlassButton from "../components/GlassButton.astro";

/*
 * Facts panel content. Education intentionally omitted per the
 * brand voice rule established for the GitHub README: institutional
 * credentialing belongs on the CV, not in surface positioning copy.
 * If you want MIT Sloan listed here, add the fact and it will
 * appear in the panel automatically.
 */
const aboutFacts = [
  { label: "Based in", value: "Chicago, Illinois" },
  { label: "Experience", value: "30 years across infrastructure, architecture, advisory, and IT leadership" },
  {
    label: "Industries",
    value: [
      "Financial services",
      "Public sector",
      "Healthcare",
      "SMB technology",
      "Professional services",
    ],
  },
  {
    label: "Functions",
    value: [
      "Senior consulting",
      "IT leadership",
      "Solutions architecture",
      "Full-stack engineering",
      "AI strategy",
    ],
  },
  {
    label: "Current focus",
    value: [
      "AI Adoption",
      "Workplace Modernization",
      "Microsoft 365 environments",
      "Cloud modernization",
    ],
  },
  { label: "Coverage", value: "North America, remote-first, travel as engagements require" },
  { label: "Open to", value: "Senior consulting engagements and IT leadership roles" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — P. R. Manjee"
  description="P. R. Manjee. Senior Technology Consultant based in Chicago. Workplace Modernization through AI Adoption and Digital Transformation for SMB, Mid-Market, and Enterprise.">
  <article class="about">
    <PageHeader
      pageTitle="About"
      meta="Senior Technology Consultant. Workplace Modernization through AI Adoption and Digital Transformation."
    />

    {/*
      Lede paragraph: matches the social card composition's positioning
      statement. Acts as the page's brand anchor at the top of the
      reading surface. Slightly larger than body copy to function as
      a lead-in.
    */}
    <p class="about-lede">
      Thirty years of building technology that sticks, from electrons to executive
      strategy. I help SMB, mid-market, and enterprise organizations modernize how
      their teams actually work, then ship the technical execution to get them there.
    </p>

    {/* Two-column body: narrative left, facts right. */}
    <div class="about-body">
      <div class="about-narrative">
        <p>
          I started in the wires. Cable runs in network closets, command-line debugging,
          weekend cutovers at three in the morning because that was when the maintenance
          windows landed. Thirty years later I still know what's actually happening at
          the infrastructure layer when an enterprise architect waves their hands at a
          Visio diagram. That foundation matters, because most of the AI and digital
          transformation work I do today still grounds out at infrastructure, identity,
          and data flow. Strategy that ignores those layers does not ship.
        </p>

        <p>
          The career arc moved from infrastructure to solutions architecture to advisory
          and IT leadership roles. Same throughline the whole way. I get called when the
          existing approach has stopped working and the team needs someone who can both
          think strategically about where to go and ship the technical work to get there.
          Bridge-builder, not specialist.
        </p>

        <p>
          What that looks like in a real engagement: a mid-market CFO knows their team
          needs better tooling but does not know which AI investments will actually move
          the business and which are theater. I help leadership separate the two. Then
          I work with their people to adopt the tools that survived the cut, without
          throwing the existing org chart in the trash. Pragmatic, not utopian.
          Outcomes first.
        </p>

        <p>
          Today's work centers on Workplace Modernization for SMB, mid-market, and
          enterprise organizations. AI Adoption is one of two primary execution paths,
          the other being Digital Transformation of the underlying systems and processes.
          Both methods serve the same goal: a workplace where employees are more
          productive, processes are more efficient, and the organization can actually
          compete at the speed the market now expects.
        </p>

        <p>
          I am based in Chicago and work primarily remotely with travel as engagements
          require. The longest client relationships I have had run six to eight years
          because I do what I said I would and tell the truth about what is working
          and what is not.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="about-facts">
        <FactsPanel facts={aboutFacts} title="At a glance" />
      </aside>
    </div>

    {/*
      Background section: expanded version of the README's career-spanning
      pattern. Full width below the two-column body so the longer-form
      thinking can breathe.
    */}
    <section class="about-background">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Background and approach</h2>

      <p>
        Industries I have worked across include financial services, public sector,
        healthcare, SMB technology, and professional services. Each one has its own
        regulatory posture, its own legacy stack, its own pace of change. The pattern
        is consistent across all of them: someone at the leadership table has decided
        the way they are working today will not get them to where they need to be in
        eighteen months, and they need outside help to figure out what to change and
        how to change it without breaking what currently works.
      </p>

      <p>
        My job is to be useful at both ends of that. I can sit in the strategy
        conversation with the executive sponsor and design the roadmap. I can also
        sit at the keyboard at two in the morning during a critical migration and
        write the PowerShell that unblocks the team. Most consultants who can do
        the first cannot do the second. Most engineers who can do the second do not
        get invited to the first. The combination is the differentiator.
      </p>

      <p>
        The current AI moment in particular is full of people who can write impressive
        slide decks about agentic workflows but cannot actually wire one up. There is
        also no shortage of engineers who can ship a working prototype but cannot
        explain to the CFO why the prototype matters. I work in the gap between those
        two failure modes. That is what I am being paid for.
      </p>
    </section>

    {/*
      Engagement band: hybrid neutral-with-soft-scarcity per choice C.
      Frames availability honestly without manufactured urgency, while
      signaling selectivity through the "small number per quarter"
      phrasing. Buttons go to the most direct contact paths.
    */}
    <section class="about-engagement">
      <GlassPanel size="lg" class="engagement-panel" padded={false}>
        <h2 class="engagement-heading">Working together</h2>
        <p class="engagement-body">
          Currently taking on a small number of engagements per quarter to ensure
          each one gets the attention it deserves. Reach out early in your evaluation
          process so we have time to talk through fit before commitments need to be
          made on either side.
        </p>
        <div class="engagement-actions">
          <GlassButton href="mailto:princemanjee@gmail.com" variant="primary" size="md">
            Start a conversation
          </GlassButton>
          <GlassButton href="https://cv.princerehman.com" variant="secondary" size="md">
            View CV
          </GlassButton>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement-links" aria-label="External profiles">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/princemanjee/" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/princemanjee" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="https://cv.princerehman.com" rel="noopener">CV</a>
        </div>
      </GlassPanel>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  /*
   * Lede paragraph: larger than body copy so it functions as the lead
   * positioning statement after the header. Uses Cormorant Garamond to
   * carry the same display tone as the brand name, with relaxed line
   * height so the longer sentences breathe.
   */
  .about-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    color: var(--color-fg-primary);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }

  /*
   * Two-column body: 1.6fr narrative, 1fr facts panel.
   * The narrative gets the majority of the width because reading-flow
   * paragraphs are the primary content. The facts panel stays compact
   * on the right as a scannable reference.
   */
  .about-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.6fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-narrative p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-fg-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg) 0;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .about-narrative p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Right column facts panel: sticky to top so it stays in view as user reads */
  .about-facts {
    position: sticky;
    top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  /*
   * Background section: full width below the two-column body.
   * Uses a wider max-width on paragraphs since it is full-bleed.
   */
  .about-background {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    color: var(--color-fg-primary);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .about-background p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-fg-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg) 0;
    max-width: 76ch;
  }

  .about-background p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /*
   * Engagement band: glass panel call-to-action at the bottom of the
   * page. Generous padding because this is where prospects make the
   * decision to reach out.
   */
  .about-engagement {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  :global(.engagement-panel) {
    padding: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .engagement-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-fg-primary);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .engagement-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-fg-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl) 0;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .engagement-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .engagement-links {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
  }

  .engagement-links a {
    color: var(--color-fg-secondary);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition:
      border-color var(--duration-fast) var(--easing-out),
      color var(--duration-fast) var(--easing-out);
  }

  .engagement-links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-fg-primary);
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-fg-primary);
  }

  .engagement-links span {
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
  }

  /* Tablet: tighter columns */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .about-body {
      grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-2xl);
    }
  }

  /* Mobile: stack columns, smaller display sizes */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about {
      padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
    }
    .about-lede {
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    }
    .about-body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-2xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    }
    .about-facts {
      position: static;
    }
    .section-heading {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }
    :global(.engagement-panel) {
      padding: var(--space-xl);
    }
    .engagement-heading {
      font-size: var(--text-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
